2013 YEONHYANG TEMPLE CUISINE RETREAT
NOV. 15 TO 22, 2013

3
00:01:31,021 --> 00:01:33,816
MOTHER JOO KYUNG-HEE,
REMEMBERED BY JOO IN-A

4
00:01:38,570 --> 00:01:41,281
Mom's resting place
has such crisp air.

5
00:02:00,926 --> 00:02:04,596
Mister, untie me!
Let me go right now!

6
00:02:04,638 --> 00:02:05,931
What are you doing to me?

7
00:02:06,014 --> 00:02:07,975
Mister, let me go!

8
00:02:08,058 --> 00:02:09,184
I have to get out of here!

9
00:02:09,268 --> 00:02:11,145
- I have to leave!
- Mom!

10
00:02:11,270 --> 00:02:12,646
- I have to get out!
- Mom!

11
00:02:12,730 --> 00:02:15,190
Untie me right now!

12
00:02:15,441 --> 00:02:17,776
What are you doing? No! Don't!

13
00:02:17,818 --> 00:02:21,613
- Hold on to her tight.
- No! Let me go!

14
00:02:22,448 --> 00:02:23,907
- Grab her tightly!
- No!

15
00:02:28,996 --> 00:02:31,039
Jumping from there
will cause too much trouble.

16
00:02:34,042 --> 00:02:35,627
You'll land smack on a hiking trail.

17
00:02:36,670 --> 00:02:39,298
It must've been a long walk up here.

18
00:02:40,340 --> 00:02:43,010
Why don't you put that will
and energy toward trying to live?

19
00:02:44,386 --> 00:02:45,679
Enjoy the clean air and go home.

20
00:02:45,763 --> 00:02:47,431
The walk down is much nicer.

21
00:03:06,158 --> 00:03:08,577
I think you missed the last bus.

22
00:03:10,120 --> 00:03:12,247
Are there really no more buses today?

23
00:03:12,831 --> 00:03:13,916
Where are you headed?

24
00:03:14,792 --> 00:03:16,418
- I'll drop you off.
- I'm too afraid

25
00:03:16,502 --> 00:03:18,921
to accept a ride from someone
who just tried to end his life.

26
00:03:19,463 --> 00:03:20,547
No, thank you.

27
00:03:22,341 --> 00:03:23,634
You have a point.

28
00:03:26,512 --> 00:03:27,471
Excuse me.

29
00:03:28,722 --> 00:03:30,098
I hope to see you again alive.

30
00:03:47,491 --> 00:03:48,575
Hello.

31
00:03:48,659 --> 00:03:51,245
I'm Lee Tae-kwon, the new recruit.

32
00:03:51,370 --> 00:03:52,371
I hope we all get along.

33
00:03:54,623 --> 00:03:56,750
There's one last person to introduce.

34
00:03:56,834 --> 00:04:00,462
Joo In-a beat her competition
for first place

35
00:04:00,546 --> 00:04:02,339
among her batch of new recruits.

36
00:04:02,464 --> 00:04:03,715
She's a true elite.

37
00:04:03,924 --> 00:04:06,426
I'll show what a first-place recruit
can do. Thank you.

38
00:04:07,094 --> 00:04:08,220
I hope we work well together.

39
00:04:13,517 --> 00:04:14,643
Cheers.

40
00:04:15,602 --> 00:04:16,645
Good job.

41
00:04:26,071 --> 00:04:28,782
Why is this group so silent?

42
00:04:30,826 --> 00:04:34,371
Ms. Joo, pour Mr. Jeon a drink.

43
00:04:34,496 --> 00:04:35,497
Oh, sure.

44
00:05:01,565 --> 00:05:03,817
So I heard you're the son
of Haemu Group's president.

45
00:05:04,276 --> 00:05:06,028
A third-generation chaebol heir
I’d only heard about.

46
00:05:09,364 --> 00:05:12,284
Then you must know
I'm not valued much as a son.

47
00:05:15,746 --> 00:05:17,414
Was that why you were struggling

48
00:05:17,539 --> 00:05:18,957
when we crossed paths back then?

49
00:05:22,044 --> 00:05:23,420
I hope we work well together

50
00:05:23,670 --> 00:05:24,713
Manager Jeon Jae-yeol.

51
00:05:33,180 --> 00:05:34,598
I really hoped to see you again.

52
00:05:37,142 --> 00:05:38,268
I'm glad I chose to live.

53
00:05:49,988 --> 00:05:51,281
What do you mean?

54
00:05:51,907 --> 00:05:55,202
Mr. Jeon headed this project
from the initial planning stage.

55
00:05:55,285 --> 00:05:56,870
It just need to be signed
to be approved

56
00:05:56,954 --> 00:05:58,246
and you want me
to omit Mr. Jeon's name?

57
00:05:58,330 --> 00:06:01,416
Ms. Joo, you need to see
the big picture here.

58
00:06:01,917 --> 00:06:03,543
Don't you see his stepbrother

59
00:06:03,627 --> 00:06:05,921
has been taking all the credit
since he joined the company?

60
00:06:07,089 --> 00:06:09,257
So what? Are you saying that's okay?

61
00:06:10,884 --> 00:06:13,470
- If the president were to hear...
- Oh, come on.

62
00:06:13,679 --> 00:06:16,848
All this is possible
because the president is allowing it.

63
00:06:19,476 --> 00:06:20,644
You've heard, haven't you?

64
00:06:21,186 --> 00:06:22,437
About Mr. Jeon's birth mother.

65
00:06:22,771 --> 00:06:24,439
He won't ever make it.

66
00:06:24,523 --> 00:06:27,025
We must side
with his younger brother.

67
00:06:27,776 --> 00:06:30,320
Fly to Dubai and close the deal.
There's a flight in two hours.

68
00:06:30,445 --> 00:06:32,114
- You need to hurry.
- In-a.

69
00:06:33,365 --> 00:06:35,117
This will only get you in trouble.

70
00:06:36,201 --> 00:06:39,079
This isn't even my project.

71
00:06:39,579 --> 00:06:40,622
It's the company's.

72
00:06:42,916 --> 00:06:44,418
Still, it's too unfair and wrong.

73
00:06:44,501 --> 00:06:46,294
You did all the hard work.

74
00:06:47,963 --> 00:06:49,172
It's enough for me
that you know that.

75
00:06:57,389 --> 00:07:01,101
Everyone's too cruel.
They're so mean and nasty.

76
00:07:02,144 --> 00:07:03,228
In-a.

77
00:07:07,065 --> 00:07:08,066
I swear

78
00:07:09,818 --> 00:07:11,903
I'll protect you
for as long as I'm here.

79
00:07:12,738 --> 00:07:14,656
Whatever happens,
even if the sky falls...

80
00:07:17,659 --> 00:07:19,327
I'll be on your side, Jae-yeol.

81
00:07:25,709 --> 00:07:27,502
This is so darn infuriating.

82
00:07:41,349 --> 00:07:42,392
So you were a couple.

83
00:07:45,228 --> 00:07:46,772
We were once a couple.

84
00:07:50,484 --> 00:07:51,485
Why did you break up?

85
00:07:53,403 --> 00:07:54,446
Just because

86
00:07:55,197 --> 00:07:58,200
he found someone
within his league to marry

87
00:07:58,825 --> 00:08:00,202
and I wanted to live
a life of my own.

88
00:08:01,203 --> 00:08:02,537
It's one of those boring
and obvious reasons.

89
00:08:03,246 --> 00:08:04,331
It's all in the past.

90
00:08:05,916 --> 00:08:06,917
Are you sure of that?

91
00:08:08,835 --> 00:08:09,836
What does that mean?

92
00:08:18,303 --> 00:08:19,471
There was a tip-off

93
00:08:20,305 --> 00:08:22,974
claiming you were having
an inappropriate workplace affair.

94
00:08:23,850 --> 00:08:26,394
That's you and the VP, isn't it?

95
00:08:54,673 --> 00:08:55,674
You came back.

96
00:08:55,924 --> 00:08:58,718
It has been a long time,
Vice President Jeon.

97
00:09:03,765 --> 00:09:04,975
I missed you.

98
00:09:09,187 --> 00:09:11,064
I think it was the day
I returned to the head office.

99
00:09:12,691 --> 00:09:14,818
He was just pleased to see me again.
It didn't mean anything else.

100
00:09:18,155 --> 00:09:19,489
It didn't mean anything?

101
00:09:20,782 --> 00:09:22,159
The situation I just witnessed

102
00:09:23,785 --> 00:09:25,120
would signify otherwise.

103
00:09:27,205 --> 00:09:29,833
Is this the vice president's
one-sided feeling?

104
00:09:31,084 --> 00:09:32,085
Or is there

105
00:09:33,420 --> 00:09:35,130
something left between you two?

106
00:10:02,741 --> 00:10:04,910
I don't want you to come here
whenever you please.

107
00:10:08,038 --> 00:10:09,748
- In-a.
- Take your hands off me.

108
00:10:11,124 --> 00:10:12,167
Let go.

109
00:10:18,673 --> 00:10:20,300
The VP and I...

110
00:10:21,593 --> 00:10:23,303
He's an executive,
and I'm just his subordinate.

111
00:10:23,803 --> 00:10:25,222
That's all it is.

112
00:10:25,764 --> 00:10:27,390
I have no residual feelings
toward him.

113
00:10:34,856 --> 00:10:36,733
To be honest, I suspected you
after I got the tip-off.

114
00:10:37,609 --> 00:10:40,028
So I investigated about you
and tailed you.

115
00:10:40,695 --> 00:10:42,405
I even followed you home
for a stakeout.

116
00:10:46,034 --> 00:10:47,035
I knew it.

117
00:10:47,577 --> 00:10:48,828
There's a reason you're the ace.

118
00:10:49,037 --> 00:10:51,957
I never imagined
the guy would turn out to be the VP.

119
00:10:53,959 --> 00:10:54,960
So, what now?

120
00:10:56,795 --> 00:10:59,297
What's your conclusion
as the handler of PM cases?

121
00:11:09,516 --> 00:11:10,558
I don't know.

122
00:11:12,769 --> 00:11:14,020
I want to believe

123
00:11:15,563 --> 00:11:17,232
everything you say at face value

124
00:11:18,942 --> 00:11:20,318
that it's all in the past

125
00:11:20,735 --> 00:11:23,113
and however the VP feels about you

126
00:11:23,989 --> 00:11:25,532
you feel nothing for him now.

127
00:11:26,616 --> 00:11:27,617
But...

128
00:11:29,327 --> 00:11:31,705
I think it's my heart
that wants to believe that.

129
00:11:38,253 --> 00:11:39,587
Give me some time.

130
00:11:40,797 --> 00:11:42,382
I'll think about it
as cool-headed as possible.

131
00:12:29,846 --> 00:12:33,266
EPISODE 7:
TO HER LOVER

132
00:12:37,312 --> 00:12:39,481
- Five packs of soju cups.
- Five packs of soju cups.

133
00:12:39,606 --> 00:12:42,359
- And five packs of paper cups.
- Five of those.

134
00:12:42,484 --> 00:12:44,944
- Two packs of plastic spoons.
- Oh, and seltzer water.

135
00:12:45,028 --> 00:12:46,029
- Seltzer water?
- Yes.

136
00:12:46,112 --> 00:12:47,614
- We didn't order any.
- For highballs.

137
00:12:47,697 --> 00:12:49,991
Okay, add seltzer to the list.

138
00:12:50,325 --> 00:12:52,077
And then...

139
00:12:52,160 --> 00:12:54,704
Mr. Moo, can you stay still?

140
00:12:54,788 --> 00:12:56,331
I'm finding it hard to focus already.

141
00:12:56,414 --> 00:12:59,084
I guess I'm excited. We haven't
held any workshop in a while.

142
00:12:59,667 --> 00:13:01,252
