It wouldn't feel right.

145
00:13:06,424 --> 00:13:07,717
Don't you think, White Blood Cell?

146
00:13:07,801 --> 00:13:09,135
You're right. It wouldn't feel right.

147
00:13:09,219 --> 00:13:10,887
- Right?
- Hae-young.

148
00:13:11,012 --> 00:13:14,057
Eleven people will drive there,
and the rest will take the bus.

149
00:13:14,182 --> 00:13:15,308
Okay.

150
00:13:15,392 --> 00:13:16,601
Send a list of names

151
00:13:16,684 --> 00:13:18,603
- to the bus driver.
- Okay.

152
00:13:19,354 --> 00:13:22,607
When did you two
get close enough to speak casually?

153
00:13:22,690 --> 00:13:24,025
You caught on real slow.

154
00:13:24,526 --> 00:13:26,694
Mr. Cha, did you finish
your tasks for the day?

155
00:13:26,778 --> 00:13:27,987
Why are you over here?

156
00:13:28,071 --> 00:13:30,240
Did you text the whole office?

157
00:13:30,365 --> 00:13:32,909
I will right now.
Gosh, I'm sick of your nagging.

158
00:13:33,701 --> 00:13:37,122
Hae-young. We should order
pork belly and pork neck.

159
00:13:37,205 --> 00:13:38,415
Okay, fine.

160
00:13:38,540 --> 00:13:39,707
- Will you order some?
- Yes.

161
00:13:39,791 --> 00:13:42,419
- Yes, buy some pork. A big chunk.
- Just pork neck.

162
00:14:07,777 --> 00:14:10,029
Assistant Manager Noh Ki-jun, is it?

163
00:14:11,239 --> 00:14:12,282
Can he be trusted?

164
00:14:12,991 --> 00:14:14,242
He's an arrogant punk.

165
00:14:16,911 --> 00:14:19,164
He's definitely not
the submissive type.

166
00:14:21,249 --> 00:14:22,584
What did he mean?

167
00:14:23,001 --> 00:14:24,544
That something that can't work
still can work.

168
00:14:25,044 --> 00:14:26,463
What cannot work

169
00:14:27,380 --> 00:14:28,715
and what can work?

170
00:14:31,134 --> 00:14:33,094
You're Haemu Group's vice president.

171
00:14:33,636 --> 00:14:35,305
Why would you mind a lowly employee?

172
00:14:35,889 --> 00:14:37,390
You must have
other important matters.

173
00:15:01,122 --> 00:15:02,123
Ms. Joo.

174
00:15:02,707 --> 00:15:05,376
- Yes, Hae-young.
- Haemu issued new credit cards.

175
00:15:05,460 --> 00:15:06,961
Give me your old one. I'll cut it up.

176
00:15:07,378 --> 00:15:09,631
- It's in my bag. I'll get it.
- Okay, thank you.

177
00:15:25,563 --> 00:15:26,606
See?

178
00:15:27,941 --> 00:15:28,983
Something that can't work

179
00:15:30,527 --> 00:15:31,819
still can work.

180
00:15:53,591 --> 00:15:56,344
Does that issue have to wait
until the next meeting?

181
00:15:56,553 --> 00:15:58,179
It is a bit too early to bring up

182
00:15:58,304 --> 00:16:01,015
although what you want
is what matters most.

183
00:16:03,101 --> 00:16:06,020
You met with Director Han, right?

184
00:16:06,104 --> 00:16:07,188
Yes, I did.

185
00:16:18,700 --> 00:16:19,742
Noh Ki-jun.

186
00:16:20,451 --> 00:16:21,828
Will you knock first?

187
00:16:23,246 --> 00:16:24,706
I'm cooking ramyeon.
Do you want some?

188
00:16:25,039 --> 00:16:26,165
No.

189
00:16:26,541 --> 00:16:29,043
- Don't you dare ask for a bite.
- Hey, A-jeong.

190
00:16:31,421 --> 00:16:34,090
What's your VP like?

191
00:16:36,801 --> 00:16:40,096
Why do you say "your VP"?
He's yours, too.

192
00:16:42,390 --> 00:16:43,391
You're right.

193
00:16:44,350 --> 00:16:45,518
He's my boss, too.

194
00:16:45,727 --> 00:16:47,353
Why are you
suddenly asking about him?

195
00:16:47,812 --> 00:16:51,065
I thought you were
trying to figure out Joo In-a.

196
00:16:52,275 --> 00:16:55,445
You rushed out saying
you wanted to figure out

197
00:16:55,528 --> 00:16:56,738
your relationship with her.

198
00:16:58,239 --> 00:16:59,282
Did you figure it out?

199
00:16:59,407 --> 00:17:01,242
I figured out one thing for sure.

200
00:17:02,660 --> 00:17:03,995
That she's a darn tough woman.

201
00:17:05,121 --> 00:17:07,457
- What does that mean?
- I don't know. Forget it.

202
00:17:07,915 --> 00:17:09,167
Enjoy your ramyeon.

203
00:17:12,211 --> 00:17:13,254
What the heck?

204
00:17:35,109 --> 00:17:36,361
HAEMU GROUP

205
00:17:36,444 --> 00:17:39,489
2025 HAEMU GROUP
STRATEGIC PLANNING JOINT WORKSHOP

206
00:17:39,572 --> 00:17:41,908
HAEMU TRAINING CENTER

207
00:17:48,373 --> 00:17:50,249
- Oh, dear.
- My goodness.

208
00:17:53,961 --> 00:17:56,130
Gosh. Are we doing a barbecue?

209
00:17:56,255 --> 00:17:59,509
Of course, Ms. Joo.
A barbecue is a must at a workshop.

210
00:17:59,592 --> 00:18:01,803
I like the way you think, Mr. Moo.

211
00:18:02,762 --> 00:18:04,180
- I'll help with the stuff.
- What?

212
00:18:04,722 --> 00:18:05,973
- No!
- Don't!

213
00:18:06,057 --> 00:18:08,601
Let me pretend to be
an easygoing boss.

214
00:18:08,685 --> 00:18:09,811
- But...
- Oh, gosh...

215
00:18:10,228 --> 00:18:13,356
That must weigh at least 20kg.
She's pretty strong.

216
00:18:13,481 --> 00:18:15,692
- Move the boxes now.
- Yes, sir.

217
00:18:24,992 --> 00:18:26,869
You have a clinical condition
of acting tough.

218
00:18:29,539 --> 00:18:31,290
STRATEGIC PLANNING JOINT WORKSHOP

219
00:18:35,837 --> 00:18:38,047
A TIME TO CONNECT TO GROW

220
00:18:38,131 --> 00:18:39,173
The Planning Team.

221
00:18:39,924 --> 00:18:40,967
Human Resources.

222
00:18:41,884 --> 00:18:43,177
And the Audit Team.

223
00:18:45,138 --> 00:18:47,724
I just said your team names,
and I'm shuddering in fear.

224
00:18:50,727 --> 00:18:53,688
You work so hard
to keep our company going.

225
00:18:54,230 --> 00:18:55,732
At this workshop

226
00:18:56,274 --> 00:18:58,401
I hope you can forget
your strenuous workplace

227
00:18:58,526 --> 00:19:00,153
and relax and have a good time.

228
00:19:13,750 --> 00:19:16,043
Hang on. Why aren't you in bed?

229
00:19:16,294 --> 00:19:18,421
Isn't it almost midnight
where you are?

230
00:19:18,546 --> 00:19:20,923
I'm exhausted. Mom nags too much.

231
00:19:21,048 --> 00:19:23,301
Can't you just do as she says?

232
00:19:23,384 --> 00:19:25,762
She said she's been having headaches.

233
00:19:26,053 --> 00:19:27,096
Okay?

234
00:19:27,180 --> 00:19:29,223
Sleep well.
I'll talk to you tomorrow.

235
00:19:32,727 --> 00:19:36,063
Mr. Ahn, you should
take time off work soon

236
00:19:36,147 --> 00:19:37,982
to fly to the US to see your family.

237
00:19:38,274 --> 00:19:39,942
I didn't know you were watching.

238
00:19:40,568 --> 00:19:41,569
It's a pleasing sight.

239
00:19:42,195 --> 00:19:44,155
Are the others getting ready
for the next program?

240
00:19:44,238 --> 00:19:47,366
Oh, we'd initially planned
a team-building exercise

241
00:19:47,450 --> 00:19:48,785
but the two team heads said

242
00:19:48,910 --> 00:19:51,329
playing a sport is the best way
to boost teamwork.

243
00:19:53,581 --> 00:19:56,751
2025 HAEMU
STRATEGIC PLANNING JOINT WORKSHOP

244
00:20:00,254 --> 00:20:02,089
Warm up well and properly
so you don't get injured.

245
00:20:07,178 --> 00:20:09,806
Can't we watch an educational video
instead of playing futsal?

246
00:20:10,765 --> 00:20:12,433
Haven't you heard, Ms. Yoon?

247
00:20:13,226 --> 00:20:16,437
Ms. Joo said the MVP of today's match
can take the day off tomorrow.

248
00:20:22,568 --> 00:20:23,903
What are you doing?

249
00:20:26,239 --> 00:20:28,616
My gosh. What's gotten into you now?

250
00:20:30,243 --> 00:20:31,828
Why are you suddenly so eager now?

251
00:20:33,871 --> 00:20:35,706
- Faster!
- Goodness.

252
00:20:35,790 --> 00:20:37,124
I see you don't exercise much.

253
00:20:38,793 --> 00:20:39,877
Okay, everyone.

254
00:20:40,461 --> 00:20:42,046
Both men and women will play

255
00:20:42,129 --> 00:20:44,131
- so be sure no one gets hurt, okay?
- Yes, ma'am.

256
00:20:44,215 --> 00:20:46,676
Don't do anything
too aggressive like tackling.

257
00:20:46,801 --> 00:20:49,512
- Let's put safety first.
- Okay.

258
00:20:49,595 --> 00:20:51,556
We can't do that
if we're playing a competitive sport.

259
00:20:51,639 --> 00:20:53,015
It's all about winning.

260
00:20:53,099 --> 00:20:55,059
Take one of these beforehand.

261
00:20:55,309 --> 00:20:58,187
- Let's build some energy first.
- Thank you.

262
00:20:58,271 --> 00:20:59,522
- "Build energy"?
- Thank you.

263
00:20:59,605 --> 00:21:01,232
Energy is an asset, too, these days.

264
00:21:01,315 --> 00:21:04,569
We must save up when we can
to use when we must.

265
00:21:04,652 --> 00:21:07,238
- Thank you.
- At a moment like this.

266
00:21:10,366 --> 00:21:11,826
- Here.
- Thank you.

267
00:21:14,745 --> 00:21:15,997
Thank you.

268
00:21:23,170 --> 00:21:25,214
Wait, what's going on?

269
00:21:25,506 --> 00:21:27,008
Are you not going to share?

270
00:21:27,592 --> 00:21:30,636
Isn't this against the rules?
Isn't this a foul?

271
00:21:31,679 --> 00:21:32,847
Hello, sir!

272
00:21:33,097 --> 00:21:34,223
- Hello.
- Hello, sir.

273
00:21:34,348 --> 00:21:35,933
- Hello, sir.
- Hello.

274
00:21:36,392 --> 00:21:37,727
Mr. Jeon, sir.

275
00:21:38,060 --> 00:21:40,229
I thought you'd left
after the opening speech.

276
00:21:41,022 --> 00:21:43,774
I heard you'd planned something fun,
so I decided to come cheer you on.

277
00:21:43,858 --> 00:21:46,485
Will you be rooting
for the Audit Team?

278
00:21:46,569 --> 00:21:47,778
Of course not.

279
00:21:48,279 --> 00:21:49,864
You'll be cheering for HR, right?

280
00:21:49,947 --> 00:21:52,783
Let's see. I'm thinking of supporting
whichever is the winning team.

281
00:21:55,912 --> 00:21:57,038
That'll be our Audit Team.

282
00:21:58,331 --> 00:22:00,041
- That's no fun.
- What?

283
00:22:03,252 --> 00:22:05,421
Ignoring the process
and siding with the winner.

284
00:22:05,922 --> 00:22:06,923
Isn't that uncool?

285
00:22:11,928 --> 00:22:14,472
You speak as if you're the winner.

286
00:22:15,473 --> 00:22:16,515
Yes.

287
00:22:18,059 --> 00:22:19,352
Because I will win.

288
00:22:24,065 --> 00:22:27,693
Mr. Noh is excessively competitive.

289
00:22:28,945 --> 00:22:30,988
I don't think we can be teammates.

290
00:22:31,864 --> 00:22:33,199
How about we compete for real?

291
00:22:34,241 --> 00:22:36,494
Sir, are you really joining
the match?

292
00:22:36,911 --> 00:22:38,621
You have a meeting at 3 p.m.

293
00:22:38,996 --> 00:22:40,081
Cancel it.

294
00:23:06,232 --> 00:23:07,483
Kick it! Score a goal!

295
00:23:10,361 --> 00:23:11,362
What the...

296
00:23:12,613 --> 00:23:14,323
- Shoot.
- Stop! Stop it!

297
00:23:15,366 --> 00:23:16,659
- Ki-jun!
- Watch out!

298
00:23:17,368 --> 00:23:18,452
Kick it.

299
00:23:29,130 --> 00:23:31,007
Mr. Jeon! No!

300
00:23:31,132 --> 00:23:32,842
Mr. Jeon, are you all right?

301
00:23:32,925 --> 00:23:35,219
Are you okay, sir?
I told you to play nice!

302
00:23:35,302 --> 00:23:36,679
What should we do about you?

303
00:23:36,762 --> 00:23:39,515
What got into Mr. Noh?
Doesn't he know he should give in?

304
00:23:39,807 --> 00:23:42,351
Maybe he wants to be the MVP
to take tomorrow off.

305
00:23:42,435 --> 00:23:44,437
At this rate,
he might lose his job for good.

306
00:23:44,979 --> 00:23:46,355
It must be your leather shoes.

307
00:23:46,439 --> 00:23:47,690
- Wear my trainers.
- No, it's fine.

308
00:23:47,815 --> 00:23:50,735
No, please, sir. Wear mine.
That would be best for us all.

309
00:23:51,110 --> 00:23:53,612
- I'm fine.
- Mr. Noh is going too far.

310
00:24:15,509 --> 00:24:17,303
What the... Did you see that?
That was a foul!

311
00:24:17,386 --> 00:24:18,846
- Referee! Come on!
- Not a foul!

312
00:24:18,929 --> 00:24:20,681
- Get back up.
- It's not a foul.

313
00:24:20,765 --> 00:24:22,558
He didn't do anything wrong.
That was just a bump.

314
00:24:22,683 --> 00:24:23,684
Keep playing.

315
00:24:23,768 --> 00:24:24,894
That was uncalled for. It was...

316
00:24:25,019 --> 00:24:26,145
Sir, you can go ahead and score.

317
00:24:26,228 --> 00:24:28,856
- No, wait. Time out!
- What?

318
00:24:28,981 --> 00:24:31,108
Sir, go ahead. Score a goal.

319
00:24:31,192 --> 00:24:33,402
- What are you doing?
- Time out!

320
00:24:33,944 --> 00:24:35,529
You caught it all, didn't you?

321
00:24:35,613 --> 00:24:36,822
You filmed it, didn't you?

322
00:24:37,698 --> 00:24:39,533
Referee, VAR.
Let's watch the instant replay.

323
00:24:39,617 --> 00:24:41,744
- Boo.
- No, forget it.

324
00:24:41,827 --> 00:24:44,955
- Let's review the footage.
- You're being a nuisance!

325
00:24:45,039 --> 00:24:47,249
You're a nuisance.
That's uncool. Stop it.

326
00:25:05,267 --> 00:25:07,353
Let's keep things going!

327
00:25:07,436 --> 00:25:09,230
- Let's play!
- What the heck?

328
00:25:09,313 --> 00:25:10,940
Wait! That's not fair!

329
00:25:11,065 --> 00:25:12,525
Come on. Get the ball.

330
00:25:12,608 --> 00:25:13,776
- Bring it this way!
- No!

331
00:25:42,596 --> 00:25:43,681
Are you all right?

332
00:25:52,106 --> 00:25:53,774
You said you'd win at all costs.

333
00:25:55,234 --> 00:25:56,318
You must feel let down.

334
00:25:58,154 --> 00:26:00,030
Not exactly. It wasn't a fair match.

335
00:26:03,701 --> 00:26:06,453
Ms. Joo tripped you up on purpose.

336
00:26:06,954 --> 00:26:08,289
Let me apologize instead.

337
00:26:09,540 --> 00:26:11,292
In-a can be like that.

338
00:26:13,961 --> 00:26:15,337
What do you mean by "like that"?

339
00:26:16,672 --> 00:26:18,924
Oh, do you mean she has long legs?

340
00:26:21,093 --> 00:26:22,803
Do you have anyone like that?

341
00:26:23,888 --> 00:26:26,432
Someone who always takes your side
no matter what happens.

342
00:26:28,809 --> 00:26:30,811
Actually, we go way back.

343
00:26:36,775 --> 00:26:37,776
Sir.

344
00:26:39,069 --> 00:26:40,362
Are you hiding something?

345
00:26:42,156 --> 00:26:43,908
You speak too much as if to deflect.

346
00:26:44,825 --> 00:26:46,952
It looks like you're trying
to hide something from me.

347
00:27:05,471 --> 00:27:07,848
Mr. Choi got you a change of clothes.

348
00:27:08,515 --> 00:27:10,059
Shall I cancel
your evening plans, too?

349
00:27:13,020 --> 00:27:14,188
I live

350
00:27:15,231 --> 00:27:16,482
with a guy right now.

351
00:27:20,694 --> 00:27:21,695
Ms. Park.

352
00:27:23,530 --> 00:27:26,700
The nice guy you said you lived with.

353
00:27:28,410 --> 00:27:29,995
Is it Mr. Noh Ki-jun?

354
00:27:47,930 --> 00:27:48,931
What's with this?

355
00:27:50,683 --> 00:27:51,809
What the...

356
00:27:52,476 --> 00:27:54,228
Are you trying to smash the thing?

357
00:27:56,146 --> 00:27:57,273
Come and sit down.

358
00:28:03,153 --> 00:28:04,196
Take a seat.

359
00:28:10,953 --> 00:28:12,413
- Is it this foot?
- What the heck?

360
00:28:15,374 --> 00:28:16,542
It's this foot.

361
00:28:18,377 --> 00:28:19,920
- Let me see.
- No...

362
00:28:23,090 --> 00:28:25,301
It's not that swollen.

363
00:28:25,384 --> 00:28:26,593
Don't be silly.

364
00:28:27,052 --> 00:28:29,555
Look at this side.
My ankle is usually slim like this.

365
00:28:30,055 --> 00:28:31,432
What a crybaby.

366
00:28:33,809 --> 00:28:35,769
You hurt me
and now you're treating me?

367
00:28:37,062 --> 00:28:38,605
You tripped me up on purpose,
didn't you?

368
00:28:39,064 --> 00:28:40,983
How could you sabotage a teammate?

369
00:28:41,066 --> 00:28:44,320
Would the VP look bad
if he didn't get to score today?

370
00:28:44,611 --> 00:28:46,238
Why do you care so much about him?

371
00:28:46,655 --> 00:28:49,783
Your career at Haemu would've ended
if you'd gone any further.

372
00:28:50,534 --> 00:28:51,660
You should know
where to draw the line

373
00:28:51,744 --> 00:28:54,496
in front of your coworkers,
especially HR.

374
00:28:55,372 --> 00:28:56,957
Don't you know
they'd have avenged the VP

375
00:28:57,041 --> 00:28:58,667
even if the VP himself
didn't complain?

376
00:28:59,001 --> 00:29:00,127
Goodness.

377
00:29:00,961 --> 00:29:03,047
You've worked long enough
to know how things work.

378
00:29:03,964 --> 00:29:05,382
Why were you so childish out there?

379
00:29:10,846 --> 00:29:12,139
So that means you took my side

380
00:29:12,681 --> 00:29:13,766
and not the VP's.

381
00:29:15,351 --> 00:29:16,518
I'm not on anyone's side.

382
00:29:16,852 --> 00:29:20,314
I just did what a superior would do
to protect her subordinate.

383
00:29:30,657 --> 00:29:32,826
- Okay.
- What do you mean by "okay"?

384
00:29:32,910 --> 00:29:34,161
Your PM case.

385
00:29:34,995 --> 00:29:36,455
I think I can conclude it now.

386
00:29:37,164 --> 00:29:39,750
- Just like that?
- Other similar cases were closed

387
00:29:39,875 --> 00:29:42,002
without disciplinary action
when the subject denied the charges

388
00:29:42,503 --> 00:29:44,254
and no other definite proof
could be found.

389
00:29:45,839 --> 00:29:47,674
I couldn't decide

390
00:29:47,800 --> 00:29:51,053
whether I should investigate further
and drag the VP

391
00:29:51,470 --> 00:29:52,971
to the interview room to grill him.

392
00:29:55,516 --> 00:29:57,309
I realized something today.

393
00:29:59,520 --> 00:30:01,021
The way you both feel for each other

394
00:30:01,772 --> 00:30:02,898
is different.

395
00:30:08,612 --> 00:30:09,655
I believe you.

396
00:30:11,323 --> 00:30:12,408
I want to believe

397
00:30:14,993 --> 00:30:16,078
how you feel.

398
00:30:20,916 --> 00:30:22,000
How do you think

399
00:30:23,836 --> 00:30:24,878
I feel?

400
00:30:30,092 --> 00:30:31,093
What you did today...

401
00:30:32,052 --> 00:30:33,053
Was that really

402
00:30:33,887 --> 00:30:36,890
only just to protect
your subordinate?

403
00:30:44,648 --> 00:30:46,108
I showed you.

404
00:30:47,443 --> 00:30:48,569
Some things can work.

405
00:30:50,821 --> 00:30:52,406
I don't care how long it takes.

406
00:30:53,615 --> 00:30:55,576
Take a good look at your feelings.

407
00:30:58,370 --> 00:30:59,455
I'll wait.

408
00:31:19,224 --> 00:31:21,059
So Ms. Song, you were in the shower

409
00:31:21,393 --> 00:31:24,646
and it seemed like someone
filmed the shower booth, right?

410
00:31:24,730 --> 00:31:27,191
Yes, someone was clearly filming
with their cell phone.

411
00:31:28,484 --> 00:31:29,735
What did the culprit look like?

412
00:31:30,444 --> 00:31:31,570
Did you get a glimpse?

413
00:31:32,571 --> 00:31:34,948
I just got a glimpse
of the person's back

414
00:31:38,118 --> 00:31:40,954
and he was wearing
the men's T-shirt for our department.

415
00:31:44,416 --> 00:31:46,293
- So disgusting.
- That's crazy.

416
00:31:48,086 --> 00:31:49,421
An inside job.

417
00:31:51,048 --> 00:31:52,966
This is the lodging,
so there are no CCTVs around.

418
00:31:53,592 --> 00:31:54,927
Do you remember anything else?

419
00:31:55,802 --> 00:31:58,680
He must be using a white cell phone.

420
00:31:58,805 --> 00:32:01,683
What I saw was a white rectangle.

421
00:32:04,269 --> 00:32:05,312
Like a white cell phone?

422
00:32:05,395 --> 00:32:07,189
- I guess so.
- It's so gross.

423
00:32:07,314 --> 00:32:08,482
Everyone has that, right?

424
00:32:09,483 --> 00:32:10,567
This looks like

425
00:32:11,401 --> 00:32:13,111
a simple job to handle

426
00:32:14,947 --> 00:32:17,658
as long as
the male employees cooperate.

427
00:32:17,741 --> 00:32:19,243
And do what? Check their phones?

428
00:32:19,326 --> 00:32:22,996
Let's check only the white phones

429
00:32:23,163 --> 00:32:25,249
and he might have hidden
the phone he used to film with

430
00:32:25,832 --> 00:32:28,168
so we should check each room
for people's luggage.

431
00:32:31,505 --> 00:32:34,883
- You don't need to go that far...
- We need to check for sure.

432
00:32:37,177 --> 00:32:39,429
It may be an inconvenience,
but please cooperate.

433
00:32:39,513 --> 00:32:41,139
- Goodness.
- Goodness, no. We should do it.

434
00:32:41,765 --> 00:32:44,935
We cannot rule out the possibility
that the culprit is the Audit Team.

435
00:32:45,018 --> 00:32:47,688
To make it fair, let's have
one from Audit and one from HR

436
00:32:47,771 --> 00:32:49,940
conduct only the necessary amount
of verification.

437
00:32:50,023 --> 00:32:51,024
All right.

438
00:32:51,984 --> 00:32:54,403
Mr. Ahn, can you represent the HR?

439
00:32:54,695 --> 00:32:56,947
You're known to be upright and proper

440
00:32:57,030 --> 00:32:59,700
- so no one will complain.
- Yes, I understand.

441
00:33:17,884 --> 00:33:20,387
- Ms. Kim?
- Mr. Ahn, actually...

442
00:33:22,389 --> 00:33:23,432
You two look great together.

443
00:33:24,725 --> 00:33:26,852
- I didn't see anything.
- Yes, okay.

444
00:33:41,366 --> 00:33:42,909
Come on, Mr. Cha.

445
00:33:43,577 --> 00:33:46,079
You can't do this
as a member of the Audit Team.

446
00:33:55,255 --> 00:33:56,381
These were...

447
00:33:58,258 --> 00:33:59,801
These were from the barbecue.

448
00:34:04,431 --> 00:34:07,142
Never mind, Hyun-kyu.
Let's give the used ones to him.

449
00:34:07,559 --> 00:34:08,685
You can have these at home.

450
00:34:10,812 --> 00:34:11,897
Thanks.

451
00:34:22,783 --> 00:34:25,952
We searched through
the women's rooms just in case

452
00:34:26,036 --> 00:34:27,120
but couldn't find anything.

453
00:34:27,746 --> 00:34:29,581
We need to do everything we can.

454
00:34:32,626 --> 00:34:35,337
Are there no CCTVs near the entrance?

455
00:34:35,420 --> 00:34:38,840
Once the day breaks, I'll ask
the management and check right away.

456
00:34:39,174 --> 00:34:42,094
Anyway, you all worked hard
until this late.

457
00:34:42,177 --> 00:34:43,428
Let's go back and get some rest.

458
00:34:43,595 --> 00:34:45,472
All right. Great work.

459
00:34:50,143 --> 00:34:52,604
Mr. Ahn, you dropped this.

460
00:34:54,481 --> 00:34:55,941
- Oh.
- Huh?

461
00:34:56,191 --> 00:34:58,652
You smoke, Mr. Ahn? Since when?

462
00:35:00,529 --> 00:35:02,989
Once every now and then.
I smoke in secret.

463
00:35:03,699 --> 00:35:05,909
There's no need to smoke in secret
when you're at work.

464
00:35:06,535 --> 00:35:08,495
Do you want
to step out with me for a second?

465
00:35:08,787 --> 00:35:11,540
He must be using a white cell phone.

466
00:35:11,623 --> 00:35:13,625
No, I plan to quit very soon.

467
00:35:13,709 --> 00:35:15,001
Thanks, Mr. Noh. I'll have it.

468
00:35:15,711 --> 00:35:16,837
I don't want to give it back.

469
00:35:17,212 --> 00:35:18,588
- Why not?
- If you want to quit

470
00:35:18,672 --> 00:35:19,881
you should do it right away.

471
00:35:20,006 --> 00:35:21,174
Let me give you a hand.

472
00:35:21,258 --> 00:35:22,759
It's okay.
I'll quit starting tomorrow.

473
00:35:22,843 --> 00:35:25,721
No way. You need to make
these decisions right away.

474
00:35:25,846 --> 00:35:27,848
Mr. Noh, do not give it back.

475
00:35:28,181 --> 00:35:31,560
- No, ma'am.
- Gosh, you two are quite the tease.

476
00:35:31,643 --> 00:35:32,894
Give it back, Mr. Noh!

477
00:35:33,019 --> 00:35:36,231
Goodness, yes. Don't try to control
what someone else likes to do.

478
00:35:36,356 --> 00:35:38,150
And cigarettes
are quite expensive these days.

479
00:35:38,233 --> 00:35:39,234
Yes!

480
00:35:40,193 --> 00:35:41,486
This thing?

481
00:36:01,757 --> 00:36:03,467
What the...

482
00:36:04,801 --> 00:36:07,345
Why? What is it?

483
00:36:10,223 --> 00:36:12,392
Is this a camera?

484
00:36:15,687 --> 00:36:17,272
Mr. Ahn!

485
00:36:17,481 --> 00:36:18,899
I can't believe this!

486
00:36:22,611 --> 00:36:23,987
Have you lost your mind?

487
00:36:25,697 --> 00:36:27,157
Damn it.

488
00:36:34,372 --> 00:36:35,916
Look at all these.

489
00:36:37,584 --> 00:36:40,212
Looks like you didn’t care
the time or place when filming these.

490
00:36:40,462 --> 00:36:42,255
From the elevator ride to the office

491
00:36:42,380 --> 00:36:45,300
in-house cafeteria, restroom

492
00:36:45,383 --> 00:36:46,843
and the subway ride back home.

493
00:36:48,887 --> 00:36:49,888
Wait, how did you take this?

494
00:36:53,517 --> 00:36:54,601
No!

495
00:36:54,768 --> 00:36:57,354
Did you install cameras
under the staff members' desks?

496
00:36:58,438 --> 00:36:59,773
This is exactly that angle!

497
00:36:59,981 --> 00:37:02,067
Well, Ms. Joo, it's...

498
00:37:02,150 --> 00:37:03,318
How can you do this

499
00:37:03,443 --> 00:37:06,404
to your colleagues
whom you work with every single day?

500
00:37:06,655 --> 00:37:08,615
What do you take them for?

501
00:37:09,282 --> 00:37:11,076
All right. I get it.

502
00:37:12,494 --> 00:37:14,538
But I am fully cooperating, right?

503
00:37:14,913 --> 00:37:18,667
Blowing this up
won't do any good for the company.

504
00:37:18,750 --> 00:37:21,002
And it'll put our department
in a different position.

505
00:37:21,086 --> 00:37:23,296
- Think of our company's image, too.
- Sure, those are important.

506
00:37:23,755 --> 00:37:25,841
Our position and the company's image.

507
00:37:26,591 --> 00:37:27,676
That's why...

508
00:37:33,974 --> 00:37:35,684
we should blow this up
as much as we can.

509
00:37:36,101 --> 00:37:38,311
While other companies
are busy trying to cover up

510
00:37:38,520 --> 00:37:40,397
their in-house sexual assaults,
we'll be the company

511
00:37:40,480 --> 00:37:42,107
that punished
a spycam offender harshly

512
00:37:42,983 --> 00:37:44,401
to become a great example.

513
00:37:45,902 --> 00:37:46,903
Wait...

514
00:38:03,044 --> 00:38:04,087
Today

515
00:38:04,713 --> 00:38:06,965
I plan to eat at the cafeteria
for the first time in a while.

516
00:38:08,216 --> 00:38:10,302
Yes, sir. I'll call them right away.

517
00:38:10,719 --> 00:38:11,761
No.

518
00:38:12,804 --> 00:38:14,055
I'll go downstairs now.

519
00:38:19,311 --> 00:38:21,146
I don't like eating in the cafeteria.

520
00:38:21,229 --> 00:38:24,274
We have to eat so we can wrap up
Mr. Ahn's case and submit the report.

521
00:38:24,357 --> 00:38:25,525
Eat up.

522
00:38:25,650 --> 00:38:28,278
We have to eat something delicious
to work more efficiently

523
00:38:28,361 --> 00:38:29,738
and to put together a better report.

524
00:38:31,531 --> 00:38:32,782
But this is delicious.

525
00:38:33,366 --> 00:38:34,492
It's so good.

526
00:38:41,833 --> 00:38:42,876
What?

527
00:38:46,087 --> 00:38:47,213
May I join you?

528
00:38:48,798 --> 00:38:50,926
Sure, we didn't rent out the place.

529
00:38:51,217 --> 00:38:52,218
Have a seat.

530
00:39:06,232 --> 00:39:07,692
Jae-yeol is at the cafeteria?

531
00:39:07,901 --> 00:39:10,320
Yes, on top of that,
he sat with Ms. Joo

532
00:39:10,403 --> 00:39:12,822
and Mr. Noh Ki-jun
of Audit Team Three

533
00:39:12,906 --> 00:39:14,908
so it was a huge deal
in the Audit Team's office.

534
00:39:17,535 --> 00:39:19,913
My brother can be pretty sly, too.

535
00:39:20,830 --> 00:39:23,333
Well, I got to eat with Doo-gi,
the best

536
00:39:23,667 --> 00:39:24,834
of Audit Team One, didn't I?

537
00:39:26,628 --> 00:39:28,713
It's an honor, Mr. Jeon.

538
00:39:30,924 --> 00:39:32,217
How's work these days?

539
00:39:32,592 --> 00:39:34,803
Were you in charge
of our subsidiaries?

540
00:39:35,095 --> 00:39:37,430
Yes, I'm now in charge of the steels
and the pharmaceuticals.

541
00:39:40,684 --> 00:39:42,435
You're in charge
of the pharmaceuticals?

542
00:39:43,144 --> 00:39:45,021
If you're doing that now,
who used to be in charge?

543
00:39:47,357 --> 00:39:50,944
May I ask why you wish to know that?

544
00:39:51,528 --> 00:39:53,697
Well, it's not a big deal.

545
00:39:54,280 --> 00:39:56,449
Yesterday, I drank with people
from the pharmaceutical division.

546
00:39:56,741 --> 00:39:59,661
They said the Audit Team
used to pester them to death

547
00:39:59,786 --> 00:40:01,663
but not anymore these days.

548
00:40:02,622 --> 00:40:05,375
So I was wondering
if there was a power trip back then

549
00:40:05,458 --> 00:40:08,294
or if things
aren't working smoothly right now.

550
00:40:09,129 --> 00:40:10,463
But I guess
someone else was handling it.

551
00:40:11,214 --> 00:40:12,507
Yes, sir.

552
00:40:22,475 --> 00:40:24,019
I heard Mr. Noh played

553
00:40:25,020 --> 00:40:26,813
a big part
in the recent spycam incident.

554
00:40:27,230 --> 00:40:29,566
Yes, well, it's my job.

555
00:40:30,817 --> 00:40:33,486
He seems quite competent.
Why did you put him in charge of PM?

556
00:40:38,324 --> 00:40:39,451
I'm the type

557
00:40:39,909 --> 00:40:41,536
who's good at everything that I do.

558
00:40:47,083 --> 00:40:48,626
Gosh, so delicious.

559
00:41:20,909 --> 00:41:21,993
You two have

560
00:41:23,286 --> 00:41:24,871
a special relationship, don't you?

561
00:41:26,081 --> 00:41:28,458
Last time, I saw you two together
by chance

562
00:41:28,541 --> 00:41:31,044
while dropping Ms. Park off
at her place.

563
00:41:32,337 --> 00:41:34,589
Oh, is it discourteous of me

564
00:41:34,714 --> 00:41:37,175
to bring up something this personal
in front of your direct superior?

565
00:41:37,717 --> 00:41:39,302
Yes, it is discourteous.

566
00:41:42,388 --> 00:41:43,723
And what's so bad about that?

567
00:41:43,973 --> 00:41:45,558
The housing price in Seoul
has skyrocketed

568
00:41:45,642 --> 00:41:46,893
so it's nice and economical.

569
00:41:48,228 --> 00:41:49,229
You already knew?

570
00:41:50,480 --> 00:41:51,481
Of course.

571
00:41:52,774 --> 00:41:55,652
She's been to our place, too.

572
00:42:00,406 --> 00:42:01,407
Is that so?

573
00:42:05,161 --> 00:42:08,665
Since when did our company
begin to visit our employees at home?

574
00:42:18,591 --> 00:42:21,553
I'll have to ask to be excused.

575
00:42:22,095 --> 00:42:23,096
I was in the middle of work.

576
00:42:24,013 --> 00:42:25,056
Sit.

577
00:42:25,765 --> 00:42:27,600
We're sitting here at the same table

578
00:42:27,851 --> 00:42:29,769
so don't you think it's basic manners
to get up together?

579
00:42:33,106 --> 00:42:34,607
You have a point.

580
00:42:34,983 --> 00:42:36,151
I'll go with you, Mr. Noh.

581
00:42:36,568 --> 00:42:38,528
I almost forgot my manners
and sent you back alone.

582
00:42:39,279 --> 00:42:42,073
We were initially
in the middle of eating together.

583
00:42:42,615 --> 00:42:44,325
Please enjoy your lunch, you two.

584
00:42:44,450 --> 00:42:45,451
Let's go.

585
00:42:47,829 --> 00:42:48,913
Come on. Let's go.

586
00:43:02,594 --> 00:43:04,053
- Isn't it good?
- It is.

587
00:43:05,138 --> 00:43:09,142
We should never waste any food,
but I couldn't help it. What a shame.

588
00:43:10,310 --> 00:43:12,562
Anyway, this toast is really good.

589
00:43:12,645 --> 00:43:14,147
Is this your first time trying it?

590
00:43:14,230 --> 00:43:15,732
That place has been around forever.

591
00:43:16,316 --> 00:43:18,985
When I was new, the only fun I had
at work was getting this

592
00:43:19,110 --> 00:43:20,653
on my way to work
and eating it in the office.

593
00:43:21,654 --> 00:43:23,031
Did you get one
for the vice president?

594
00:43:23,948 --> 00:43:24,949
I don't know.

595
00:43:28,494 --> 00:43:30,246
He must be furious, right?

596
00:43:31,497 --> 00:43:33,416
How am I going to keep my career
in the future?

597
00:43:35,293 --> 00:43:37,503
Will you take responsibility
and protect your subordinate?

598
00:43:38,338 --> 00:43:39,797
So why did you act so cheekily?

599
00:43:41,007 --> 00:43:44,344
I mean, he was way too immature
for someone who's a vice president.

600
00:43:46,137 --> 00:43:49,766
Anyway, I can tell after today
that he's definitely still into you.

601
00:43:50,308 --> 00:43:52,518
Then what? Do you want to conduct
an additional investigation?

602
00:43:52,769 --> 00:43:55,104
No, you aren't into him,
so it doesn't matter.

603
00:43:56,606 --> 00:43:58,524
I guess some people remember

604
00:43:58,650 --> 00:44:01,194
their old relationship like the rose
from The Little Prince.

605
00:44:04,530 --> 00:44:06,950
- What do you mean by that?
- Don't you know it?

606
00:44:07,617 --> 00:44:09,118
The Little Prince comes to Earth

607
00:44:09,202 --> 00:44:11,454
and sees many roses
that are exactly the same-looking.

608
00:44:11,955 --> 00:44:13,122
Yet he returns to the planet

609
00:44:13,206 --> 00:44:15,041
where the rose
he spent time with lives.

610
00:44:16,793 --> 00:44:18,211
The Little Prince returns?

611
00:44:19,212 --> 00:44:20,588
Doesn't he live
with the fox on Earth?

612
00:44:20,672 --> 00:44:22,966
No, he returns to his planet.

613
00:44:23,549 --> 00:44:25,468
He wants to be responsible
for the rose he cultivated.

614
00:44:25,551 --> 00:44:26,719
No, he remains on Earth.

615
00:44:27,553 --> 00:44:30,390
No, he returns.
Do you want to make a bet?

616
00:44:31,557 --> 00:44:33,393
Bet? I'm in.

617
00:44:33,726 --> 00:44:35,979
We aren't betting on a wish,
but a penalty.

618
00:44:36,396 --> 00:44:37,397
Sure.

619
00:44:38,147 --> 00:44:40,441
"I'm returning to the star tonight."

620
00:44:40,566 --> 00:44:42,610
See? It means
he's returning to his planet.

621
00:44:44,529 --> 00:44:45,989
What? This is really sad.

622
00:44:47,031 --> 00:44:49,409
Why did I remember the story
as a happy ending? What is this?

623
00:44:49,826 --> 00:44:52,203
You must've interpreted this
as a happy ending back then.

624
00:44:53,663 --> 00:44:56,541
Why did he want to leave Earth
after the trouble of getting there?

625
00:45:00,420 --> 00:45:01,421
So I won, right?

626
00:45:02,755 --> 00:45:05,466
You must've been
an avid reader of children's tales.

627
00:45:07,343 --> 00:45:10,471
Admit to your defeat
and face your penalty.

628
00:45:11,973 --> 00:45:13,725
Admitted. What's the penalty?

629
00:45:16,894 --> 00:45:19,105
Now, what can I do here

630
00:45:19,647 --> 00:45:21,482
to turn this into a cruel fairy tale?

631
00:45:33,953 --> 00:45:35,079
What is it?

632
00:45:54,599 --> 00:45:57,143
Hey, Ms. Joo has finally gone cuckoo
in her head.

633
00:46:03,649 --> 00:46:05,068
Excuse me, Ms. Joo.

634
00:46:05,985 --> 00:46:08,363
Your hair...

635
00:46:11,991 --> 00:46:12,992
What about it?

636
00:46:15,161 --> 00:46:16,704
Isn't it adorable?

637
00:46:17,038 --> 00:46:19,123
I've been into these things lately.

638
00:46:26,172 --> 00:46:27,298
Get back to work.

639
00:46:43,147 --> 00:46:47,276
ART CLASS DIRECTOR

640
00:46:50,113 --> 00:46:51,322
Thank you.

641
00:46:51,531 --> 00:46:54,492
That's cute.
What in the world is that hairpin?

642
00:46:55,701 --> 00:46:58,121
Yes, right. I still had this on?

643
00:46:59,372 --> 00:47:00,498
How embarrassing.

644
00:47:00,957 --> 00:47:02,041
That's new.

645
00:47:02,500 --> 00:47:03,876
Is that the recent trend?

646
00:47:03,918 --> 00:47:06,879
No, it was a gift from someone

647
00:47:07,880 --> 00:47:09,382
as a penalty.

648
00:47:13,052 --> 00:47:14,053
Anyway.

649
00:47:15,221 --> 00:47:16,764
I don't have to come
as a model anymore?

650
00:47:17,557 --> 00:47:18,933
What's going on? Am I getting fired?

651
00:47:19,058 --> 00:47:21,227
I should've hired you officially
and paid you.

652
00:47:21,811 --> 00:47:25,398
The business has been slow,
so I've been shameless.

653
00:47:25,773 --> 00:47:28,359
Don't say that.
I did it because I wanted to.

654
00:47:29,485 --> 00:47:31,821
And you already know
that I needed this.

655
00:47:32,572 --> 00:47:33,698
Do you still need it?

656
00:47:37,076 --> 00:47:39,579
I've known you a long time, In-a.

657
00:47:40,496 --> 00:47:44,667
And lately, I've been thinking
that you might not need

658
00:47:44,750 --> 00:47:45,835
this time anymore.

659
00:47:47,044 --> 00:47:48,212
You've been laughing a lot.

660
00:47:50,173 --> 00:47:52,425
- Me?
- Yes, and you seem to be at peace.

661
00:47:54,135 --> 00:47:55,178
Tell me.

662
00:47:55,636 --> 00:47:56,929
You're seeing someone, right?

663
00:47:57,430 --> 00:47:58,931
Is it the one
who gave you that hairpin?

664
00:48:02,393 --> 00:48:04,729
No, this is way too...

665
00:48:05,396 --> 00:48:08,483
You're the flower of the Audit Team,
so why don't you put a flower on?

666
00:48:08,566 --> 00:48:09,942
All right.

667
00:48:11,944 --> 00:48:12,987
A pig.

668
00:48:13,529 --> 00:48:15,740
Next, a rabbit.

669
00:48:16,115 --> 00:48:17,241
Look to the side.

670
00:48:21,787 --> 00:48:25,166
- I can't.
- What do you mean? Why not?

671
00:48:26,584 --> 00:48:27,710
He's someone at work.

672
00:48:29,712 --> 00:48:32,882
In another country, there is
this phrase about dating at work.

673
00:48:34,008 --> 00:48:35,676
"Don't go number two where you eat."

674
00:48:37,803 --> 00:48:39,347
It means it's that insane.

675
00:48:39,430 --> 00:48:42,934
Why not? It's better than
holding it in and getting sick.

676
00:48:43,726 --> 00:48:46,395
I'm saying, who cares
if you do something crazy?

677
00:48:47,396 --> 00:48:51,275
Didn't you think this job was
also crazy before you did it?

678
00:48:51,609 --> 00:48:52,818
But after trying it

679
00:48:52,902 --> 00:48:55,029
it became the only escape
in your everyday life.

680
00:48:56,155 --> 00:48:57,823
Don't put a limit on yourself.

681
00:48:58,324 --> 00:49:02,036
Only when you break the limit
will you find new joy.

682
00:49:03,704 --> 00:49:06,582
Hey, Director.
You're good with words.

683
00:49:06,791 --> 00:49:08,042
You didn't know?

684
00:49:31,566 --> 00:49:35,152
RECREATIONAL ART CLASS
TONIGHT AT 9 P.M.

685
00:49:49,917 --> 00:49:51,669
Have I always been this pretty?

686
00:50:04,682 --> 00:50:05,725
You are pretty.

687
00:50:31,375 --> 00:50:34,086
AUDIT RESULT

688
00:50:39,342 --> 00:50:41,177
You didn't seem to eat much at lunch.

689
00:50:41,677 --> 00:50:42,803
You should have some.

690
00:50:44,597 --> 00:50:45,598
Okay.

691
00:50:46,098 --> 00:50:48,059
And you crossed the line earlier.

692
00:50:50,853 --> 00:50:52,480
You used me.

693
00:50:53,648 --> 00:50:54,774
I know that

694
00:50:55,775 --> 00:50:57,568
you like Ms. Joo In-a.

695
00:51:00,655 --> 00:51:02,615
I'm a very competent assistant

696
00:51:03,949 --> 00:51:05,785
and a woman who likes you.

697
00:51:08,454 --> 00:51:09,622
Ki-jun is

698
00:51:10,539 --> 00:51:12,041
a great guy.

699
00:51:13,668 --> 00:51:14,877
It was the first time I ran away

700
00:51:14,960 --> 00:51:16,629
feeling annoyed
that he found out about my situation

701
00:51:17,588 --> 00:51:20,132
and I didn't want to burden him.

702
00:51:20,758 --> 00:51:23,260
I didn't want to be
belittled before him.

703
00:51:31,769 --> 00:51:33,187
Why are you telling me this?

704
00:51:33,270 --> 00:51:35,940
I'm saying you have nothing on Ki-jun

705
00:51:37,983 --> 00:51:39,443
even for someone like you.

706
00:51:58,170 --> 00:52:01,257
HR REPORT
ON US EXPATRIATE

707
00:52:16,313 --> 00:52:18,023
- Enjoy.
- Thank you.

708
00:52:18,983 --> 00:52:20,609
- Two toasts, please.
- Sure.

709
00:52:20,693 --> 00:52:22,236
- Please make them delicious.
- Of course.

710
00:52:24,113 --> 00:52:26,365
- Enjoy.
- Thank you.

711
00:52:33,289 --> 00:52:34,707
What is this?

712
00:52:35,166 --> 00:52:36,542
What does he have to say now?

713
00:52:36,625 --> 00:52:38,544
HR HEAD AHN SEUNG-WOO, PERVERT

714
00:52:38,586 --> 00:52:40,254
MISSED CALLS FROM
HR HEAD AHN SEUNG-WOO, PERVERT

715
00:52:44,884 --> 00:52:48,262
Your call cannot be connected.
You will be redirected to voicemail.

716
00:52:48,387 --> 00:52:49,513
ASSISTANT MANAGER NOH KI-JUN

717
00:52:55,603 --> 00:52:57,396
Will you please pick up?

718
00:53:12,745 --> 00:53:13,746
Hey, Ki-jun!

719
00:53:13,954 --> 00:53:15,289
What's going on, man?

720
00:53:15,706 --> 00:53:17,416
You really got
on the vice president's good side.

721
00:53:17,917 --> 00:53:19,251
What are you talking about?

722
00:53:19,376 --> 00:53:21,086
Ms. Hong of HR told me everything.

723
00:53:21,170 --> 00:53:22,838
I heard you got assigned
as an expatriate to the US.

724
00:53:24,340 --> 00:53:25,341
What?

725
00:53:26,717 --> 00:53:27,802
I'm so jealous.

726
00:53:31,180 --> 00:53:33,808
Your call cannot be connected.
You will be redirected to voicemail.

727
00:53:38,145 --> 00:53:40,314
Goodness, Mr. Lee. Mr. Lee.

728
00:53:40,648 --> 00:53:42,107
Thank you for coming out
on your busy day.

729
00:53:42,817 --> 00:53:43,818
Yes.

730
00:53:50,157 --> 00:53:51,951
I can't have you keep calling me.

731
00:53:52,201 --> 00:53:54,119
Think of how desperate I am.

732
00:53:54,662 --> 00:53:56,705
I'm about to get divorced.

733
00:53:56,789 --> 00:53:58,165
My wife is now...

734
00:54:00,835 --> 00:54:03,379
She's banning me
from seeing my child, Do-yun.

735
00:54:05,548 --> 00:54:09,176
Can you help me
get a favorable arrangement

736
00:54:09,260 --> 00:54:11,470
or let me settle the case?

737
00:54:12,263 --> 00:54:14,139
Maybe the employees
can turn in petitions

738
00:54:14,181 --> 00:54:16,141
and say that I've worked hard

739
00:54:16,600 --> 00:54:18,811
and always had a great reputation.

740
00:54:19,979 --> 00:54:22,690
Well, even if I
personally made a move

741
00:54:23,482 --> 00:54:25,568
the Audit Team
is already set on this.

742
00:54:26,318 --> 00:54:30,948
I've also been
contacting Mr. Noh Ki-jun

743
00:54:31,657 --> 00:54:33,158
but he won't pick up his phone.

744
00:54:34,493 --> 00:54:37,288
Mr. Ahn, he's on a roll right now.

745
00:54:37,830 --> 00:54:40,165
He got a special promotion,
thanks to your incident

746
00:54:40,249 --> 00:54:41,834
and he even got a chance
to work in the US.

747
00:54:43,502 --> 00:54:44,545
You didn't know?

748
00:54:46,881 --> 00:54:50,175
Director Park, I hear your daughter
is getting married soon.

749
00:54:50,676 --> 00:54:51,760
Congratulations.

750
00:54:52,386 --> 00:54:54,305
Let me know when you have the date.

751
00:54:54,555 --> 00:54:56,015
I'd like to relay
my congratulatory message.

752
00:54:56,056 --> 00:54:58,684
Goodness, Director Park.
That wedding will be a big deal.

753
00:54:59,184 --> 00:55:03,480
Are you really willing to come
and share a message?

754
00:55:04,481 --> 00:55:06,692
Or do you think
a song will be better?

755
00:55:25,920 --> 00:55:28,380
Your call cannot be connected.
You will be redirected to voicemail.

756
00:55:28,589 --> 00:55:29,715
Why won't she pick up?

757
00:55:29,798 --> 00:55:30,883
JOO IN-A

758
00:55:35,012 --> 00:55:37,222
Your call cannot be connected.
You will be redirected to voicemail.

759
00:55:39,433 --> 00:55:41,810
Hey, have you seen Ms. Joo?

760
00:55:43,187 --> 00:55:44,355
Have you seen her?

761
00:55:44,813 --> 00:55:47,566
I didn't, but Seung-hee just told me

762
00:55:47,900 --> 00:55:50,819
that Ms. Joo suddenly showed up
and left with the vice president.

763
00:55:52,404 --> 00:55:53,447
Where did they go?

764
00:55:57,451 --> 00:55:58,577
What do you think you're doing?

765
00:55:58,661 --> 00:56:00,579
- What?
- About Mr. Noh Ki-jun!

766
00:56:00,704 --> 00:56:03,832
You did not say a word to him or me,
who has direct authority over him.

767
00:56:03,916 --> 00:56:05,334
How can you suddenly announce

768
00:56:05,417 --> 00:56:07,836
sending him away overnight
like he's some parcel?

769
00:56:08,045 --> 00:56:10,089
And you barged in there

770
00:56:10,506 --> 00:56:11,590
to nitpick over this?

771
00:56:12,549 --> 00:56:14,593
You dragged me out
of a meeting with the directors

772
00:56:14,677 --> 00:56:16,637
just to nitpick over
an assistant manager's position?

773
00:56:16,720 --> 00:56:18,305
It's not just his position.

774
00:56:18,389 --> 00:56:21,100
This is a matter of respect
for my duty and authority.

775
00:56:21,600 --> 00:56:23,644
You are not allowed
to appoint an employee like this

776
00:56:23,727 --> 00:56:25,270
if he has no reason
to be disciplined.

777
00:56:27,523 --> 00:56:28,983
This is unjust.

778
00:56:29,858 --> 00:56:31,068
And this calls for an audit.

779
00:56:32,027 --> 00:56:33,654
I've reviewed
the decision thoroughly.

780
00:56:34,029 --> 00:56:36,615
It's a loss to the business
for an employee with his performance

781
00:56:36,699 --> 00:56:39,034
and competence
to be cooped up doing PM duties.

782
00:56:41,787 --> 00:56:42,955
Is that really the reason

783
00:56:44,999 --> 00:56:46,792
and not because
of any personal feelings?

784
00:56:48,502 --> 00:56:49,795
It's the US expatriate position.

785
00:56:49,920 --> 00:56:52,548
That's a place
where every employee wants to go

786
00:56:52,631 --> 00:56:54,299
and it's a privilege
for an assistant manager.

787
00:56:54,842 --> 00:56:56,677
He'll also be promoted as a manager.

788
00:56:56,969 --> 00:56:58,637
Is this something
for you to be so angry over?

789
00:56:59,346 --> 00:57:02,182
In-a, don't you think
you're the one holding back

790
00:57:02,599 --> 00:57:05,060
a talented employee's career
because of your feelings?

791
00:57:06,645 --> 00:57:08,397
Can you honestly tell me

792
00:57:08,981 --> 00:57:11,316
that you are this furious
only due to official reasons?

793
00:57:16,822 --> 00:57:17,823
In-a.

794
00:57:18,824 --> 00:57:21,243
There are many decisions I can make.

795
00:57:22,327 --> 00:57:25,664
And among them, I believe I made
the most courteous one I could.

796
00:57:33,630 --> 00:57:36,341
Your call cannot be connected.
You will be redirected to voicemail.

797
00:57:37,342 --> 00:57:38,469
Mr. Noh Ki-jun.

798
00:57:42,514 --> 00:57:43,515
Mr. Ahn.

799
00:57:46,018 --> 00:57:48,687
I cannot have you visit
or contact me like this.

800
00:57:55,861 --> 00:57:57,112
Hey, you...

801
00:58:26,600 --> 00:58:28,602
EMERGENCY ROOM

802
00:59:13,272 --> 00:59:15,649
You can't drive like this.
Let me take you there.

803
00:59:33,959 --> 00:59:35,502
Is he still waiting
in the emergency room?

804
00:59:39,464 --> 00:59:41,967
No, it's okay. There's no need.
I'll call you back.

805
00:59:42,134 --> 00:59:43,552
I'll just get off here.

806
00:59:44,178 --> 00:59:45,470
It's still pretty far from here.

807
00:59:45,554 --> 00:59:48,432
Just past the intersection... In-a!

808
01:00:04,656 --> 01:00:05,866
It's heartbreaking.

809
01:00:10,746 --> 01:00:12,247
You must've been very lonely.

810
01:00:15,626 --> 01:00:17,211
You keep acting tough

811
01:00:20,005 --> 01:00:21,173
which is making it worse.

812
01:00:27,346 --> 01:00:28,513
Then will you

813
01:00:29,181 --> 01:00:30,599
answer my question...

814
01:00:38,482 --> 01:00:40,067
Why do you push me away?

815
01:00:54,039 --> 01:00:55,874
About your question, Mr. Noh...

816
01:00:57,501 --> 01:00:59,670
The real reason
why I keep pushing you away...

817
01:01:04,967 --> 01:01:06,051
I...

818
01:01:09,763 --> 01:01:10,889
I...

819
01:01:15,102 --> 01:01:18,021
FILING FOR LOVE

820
01:01:46,800 --> 01:01:49,219
Mr. Noh. I was scared. It was scary.

821
01:01:49,303 --> 01:01:52,639
I think you should come along
to the Jeju business trip, Ms. Joo.

822
01:01:52,848 --> 01:01:53,932
What are you doing?

823
01:01:54,057 --> 01:01:56,393
Are you sending an assistant manager
overseas because of your feelings?

824
01:01:56,601 --> 01:01:58,770
In-a, please just stay by my side.

825
01:01:59,187 --> 01:02:01,565
What's the real reason you sent me
to Audit Team Three?

826
01:02:02,190 --> 01:02:03,608
Was it to protect Jeon Jae-yeol?

827
01:02:03,859 --> 01:02:06,194
How do you expect me
to understand this whole situation?

828
01:02:06,278 --> 01:02:08,196
We need to talk right now!

829
01:02:08,655 --> 01:02:09,948
Oddly enough

830
01:02:10,032 --> 01:02:13,118
I have a habit of hiding the truth
when it matters most.

831
01:02:26,673 --> 01:02:28,675
Subtitles by Eunsook Youn
and Jennifer Lim

